Victoria Harbour is sheltered water in a shoreline indentation, suitable for mooring or anchoring vessels in the Juan de Fuca Strait. The dataset includes oceanographic data collected at various depths in the water column by a suite of instruments, during a single profiling deployment known as a 'cast'.
